                            <comment id="14655725" author="mbaesken" created="Fri, 8 Mar 2024 00:26:52 -0800"  >&amp;gt; From what I&amp;#39;ve read you should never retry a failed close on Linux.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Yes I think you are correct on this one. Thanks for clarifying.&lt;br/&gt;
Here I found some more discussion/information about the topic :  &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/boostorg/beast/issues/1445&quot;&gt;https://github.com/boostorg/beast/issues/1445&lt;/a&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14655654" author="dholmes" created="Thu, 7 Mar 2024 15:40:18 -0800"  >You misunderstood my query. Many system calls document EINTR but when using SA_RESTART EINTR may become impossible. If you look at &amp;quot;man -s 7 signal&amp;quot;. it lists those functions which will be restarted and those which will always report EINTR - however close() is not listed in either category.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
From what I&amp;#39;ve read you should never retry a failed close on Linux.</comment>
                            <comment id="14655497" author="mbaesken" created="Thu, 7 Mar 2024 05:22:52 -0800"  >&amp;gt; But also see &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8281673&quot; title=&quot;Re-examine RESTARTABLE uses in relation to SA_RESTART&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8281673&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8281673&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Regarding &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8281673&quot; title=&quot;Re-examine RESTARTABLE uses in relation to SA_RESTART&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8281673&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8281673&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  I wonder, should we leave RESTARTABLE with close ?   At least on Linux it was considered unwanted and was adjusted/removed e.g. in  &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8205959&quot; title=&quot;Do not restart close if errno is EINTR&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8205959&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8205959&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  .</comment>
                            <comment id="14655487" author="mbaesken" created="Thu, 7 Mar 2024 04:41:10 -0800"  >&amp;gt; But also see &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8281673&quot; title=&quot;Re-examine RESTARTABLE uses in relation to SA_RESTART&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8281673&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8281673&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. can close even produce EINTR?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The linux man page of close documents it, EINTR is listed here in the Errors part :&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/close.2.html&quot;&gt;https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/close.2.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
so I would say yes.</comment>
                            <comment id="14655476" author="dholmes" created="Thu, 7 Mar 2024 04:21:00 -0800"  >But also see &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8281673&quot; title=&quot;Re-examine RESTARTABLE uses in relation to SA_RESTART&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8281673&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8281673&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. can close even produce EINTR?</comment>
